    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://www.ontologia.fr/OTB/legal_participants">
        <dc:title>Athenian-Legal-Participants</dc:title>
        <dc:description>This is version 2.0 of a database for the PhD "Semantic Annotation and Attic Oratory" that defines the terms used to designate participants in Classical Athenian courts c. 419 BC to 323 BC. I define a legal participant as a person involved in a court proceeding without being an appointed or elected official. This work draws upon the corpus of Attic oratory as well as The Law of Ancient Athens by David D. Phillips and the Shape of Athenian Law by S.C. Todd. </dc:description>
        <dc:issued rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2025-04-02</dc:issued>
